<English>: There were some technological issues when the Hispano cannon was converted to belt feed. Among them was the fact that the chamber width was 1/16 inch too large, which allowed backflow gases to enter the barrel and jam the breechlock. Reducing the size of the chamber width helped solve the problem and lessened the amount of weapon failures.
